@page "/tos"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]
@layout BaustellenBob.Server.Components.Layout.EmptyLayout

<PageTitle>Structra - Terms of Service</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Medium" Class="py-6">
    <MudPaper Class="pa-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">Terms of Service (ToS)</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.caption" Class="mb-4">Effective date: 2026-03-09</MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">1. Scope</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            These Terms govern the use of the Structra SaaS provided by
            <strong>[FULL NAME], Sole Proprietor</strong>,
            <strong>[ADDRESS]</strong> ("Provider").
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">2. Service</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            Structra provides browser-based workflows for construction project management,
            photo documentation, and work report creation.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">3. Account and Access</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            Customers are responsible for account credentials and all activities under their account.
            Unauthorized use must be reported without delay.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">4. Fees and Subscription</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            Paid plans are billed according to the selected subscription. Unless otherwise agreed,
            subscriptions renew automatically and may be cancelled with notice of <strong>[X DAYS/WEEKS]</strong>
            before the end of the billing period.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">5. Customer Content</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            Customers retain rights to uploaded data. Customers warrant they are legally entitled
            to process and upload such data and that no third-party rights are violated.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">6. Availability and Maintenance</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            The Provider targets high availability but may perform maintenance and security updates.
            Temporary outages can occur for technical reasons.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">7. Liability</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            Liability is unlimited for intent, gross negligence, and damages related to injury to life,
            body, or health. For slight negligence, liability is limited to foreseeable, typical contractual damage.
        </MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-3">
            Liability for data loss is excluded, except in cases of intent, gross negligence, or where
            mandatory statutory law provides otherwise. The customer remains responsible for maintaining
            appropriate and regular backups of their data.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6" GutterBottom="true">8. Governing Law</MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
            These Terms are governed by German law. If the customer is a merchant,
            place of jurisdiction is <strong>[JURISDICTION]</strong>.
        </MudText>

        <MudAlert Severity="Severity.Warning" Dense="true" Variant="Variant.Outlined">
            Replace all bracketed placeholders with your real legal and business information before production use.
        </MudAlert>
    </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>
